My linux distro is Ubuntu attached to the breezy-badger update repository.

It appears as though a similar bug has been posted by another user on Ubuntu's
Bugzilla.  The bug report is located at:

http://lists.ubuntu.com/archives/ubuntu-bugs/2005-July/066932.html

It looks like if your install has been corrupted.
Try to run once with speciyfing -clean on the command line.

Running:

> eclipse -clean

resulted in the same error.  I tried running eclipse as sudo (root) and it
worked fine.  I then reinstalled eclipse-sdk from my apt-get / synaptic package
management system and I can now run eclipse as a normal user.

Looks like I was able to resolve the issue, not sure what caused the glitch in
the first place though.
Eclipse does not modify permissions of the file system :-) So closing as invalid for now. However if you happen to encounter the problem and can identify the cause let us know. thx.
